<subSubSection id="C35E49C9FFDCAE42FCCC198FC2D1FA36" pageId="1" pageNumber="264" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BFB1A42FFDCAE42FCCC198FC2D1FA36" blockId="1.[809,1452,947,1462]" pageId="1" pageNumber="264">
<emphasis id="B930C650FFDCAE42FCCC198FC59FFC4A" bold="true" box="[809,927,947,970]" pageId="1" pageNumber="264">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Mesethmoid with shallow median cleft, flanked by reduced and anteriorly rounded cornua (
<figureCitation id="137F06C7FFDCAE42FB3819E8C31BFC6B" box="[1245,1307,980,1003]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[133,172,1874,1897]" captionTargetBox="[147,1451,1016,1843]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 4. Taubateia paraiba, most anterior part of the neurocranium showing mesethmoid features: a, original fossil impression sprinkled with ammonium chloride; b, cast in latex sprinkled with ammonium chloride. Abbreviations: ac, mesethmoid anterior cornua; mc, mesethmoid crest; md, mesethmoid disk; me, mesethmoid; mmc, mesethmoid median cleft." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5419235" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5419235/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="264">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
); mesethmoid ventral disk small, ball-shaped and subterminal (
<figureCitation id="137F06C7FFDCAE42FAB319C9C39DFB8C" box="[1366,1437,1013,1036]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[133,172,1874,1897]" captionTargetBox="[147,1451,1016,1843]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 4. Taubateia paraiba, most anterior part of the neurocranium showing mesethmoid features: a, original fossil impression sprinkled with ammonium chloride; b, cast in latex sprinkled with ammonium chloride. Abbreviations: ac, mesethmoid anterior cornua; mc, mesethmoid crest; md, mesethmoid disk; me, mesethmoid; mmc, mesethmoid median cleft." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5419235" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5419235/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="264">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
); mesethmoid shaft wide (
<figureCitation id="137F06C7FFDCAE42FBC51E2BC269FBAE" box="[1056,1129,1047,1070]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[130,169,1778,1801]" captionTargetBox="[165,1431,837,1742]" captionTargetId="figure-433@3.[146,1431,837,1743]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 3. Comparison between an interpretative drawing of Taubateia paraiba (a) and a Hypostomus sp. neurocranium (b), both in ventral view. Abbreviations: acm, articular condyle for metapterygoid; af, articular facet for rib on v6; ag, aortic groove; bl, basioccipital lateral process; bo, basioccipital; cc, Weberian complex centrum; ex, exoccipital; exf, exoccipital foramina; fr, frontal; le, lateral ethmoid; ler, lateral ethmoid ridge for metapterygoid; me, mesethmoid; md, mesethmoid disk; os, orbitosphenoid; pr, prootic; ps, parasphenoid; pt, pterotic-supracleithrum; rb, rib; sp, sphenotic?; trl, transcapular ligament; tvp, transverse process of the Weberian compound centrum; v6, sixth vertebrae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5419233" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5419233/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="264">Fig. 3a</figureCitation>
); anterior tip of prevomer forms spike-like sutural joint with mesethmoid (
<figureCitation id="137F06C7FFDCAE42FB391E04C327FBCF" box="[1244,1319,1080,1103]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[130,169,1778,1801]" captionTargetBox="[165,1431,837,1742]" captionTargetId="figure-433@3.[146,1431,837,1743]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 3. Comparison between an interpretative drawing of Taubateia paraiba (a) and a Hypostomus sp. neurocranium (b), both in ventral view. Abbreviations: acm, articular condyle for metapterygoid; af, articular facet for rib on v6; ag, aortic groove; bl, basioccipital lateral process; bo, basioccipital; cc, Weberian complex centrum; ex, exoccipital; exf, exoccipital foramina; fr, frontal; le, lateral ethmoid; ler, lateral ethmoid ridge for metapterygoid; me, mesethmoid; md, mesethmoid disk; os, orbitosphenoid; pr, prootic; ps, parasphenoid; pt, pterotic-supracleithrum; rb, rib; sp, sphenotic?; trl, transcapular ligament; tvp, transverse process of the Weberian compound centrum; v6, sixth vertebrae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5419233" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5419233/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="264">Fig. 3a</figureCitation>
); posterolateral corner of the lateral ethmoid greatly expanded (
<figureCitation id="137F06C7FFDCAE42FABF1E65C3A6FBF0" box="[1370,1446,1113,1136]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[138,177,1901,1924]" captionTargetBox="[151,1445,928,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-404@2.[151,1446,928,1877]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 2. Taubateia paraiba, DGM 17-P, holotype. Shale slab with fossil impression from the Tremembé Formation, Taubaté Basin (a) and the cast in latex (b)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5419231" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5419231/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="264">Figs. 2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="137F06C7FFDCAE42FCCC1E47C544FB12" box="[809,836,1147,1170]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[130,169,1778,1801]" captionTargetBox="[165,1431,837,1742]" captionTargetId="figure-433@3.[146,1431,837,1743]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 3. Comparison between an interpretative drawing of Taubateia paraiba (a) and a Hypostomus sp. neurocranium (b), both in ventral view. Abbreviations: acm, articular condyle for metapterygoid; af, articular facet for rib on v6; ag, aortic groove; bl, basioccipital lateral process; bo, basioccipital; cc, Weberian complex centrum; ex, exoccipital; exf, exoccipital foramina; fr, frontal; le, lateral ethmoid; ler, lateral ethmoid ridge for metapterygoid; me, mesethmoid; md, mesethmoid disk; os, orbitosphenoid; pr, prootic; ps, parasphenoid; pt, pterotic-supracleithrum; rb, rib; sp, sphenotic?; trl, transcapular ligament; tvp, transverse process of the Weberian compound centrum; v6, sixth vertebrae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5419233" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5419233/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="264">3a</figureCitation>
); ventral ridge on lateral ethmoid low and rounded (
<figureCitation id="137F06C7FFDCAE42FABB1E47C3A7FB12" box="[1374,1447,1147,1170]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[138,177,1901,1924]" captionTargetBox="[151,1445,928,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-404@2.[151,1446,928,1877]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 2. Taubateia paraiba, DGM 17-P, holotype. Shale slab with fossil impression from the Tremembé Formation, Taubaté Basin (a) and the cast in latex (b)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5419231" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5419231/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="264">Figs. 2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="137F06C7FFDCAE42FCCC1EA0C544FB33" box="[809,836,1180,1203]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[130,169,1778,1801]" captionTargetBox="[165,1431,837,1742]" captionTargetId="figure-433@3.[146,1431,837,1743]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 3. Comparison between an interpretative drawing of Taubateia paraiba (a) and a Hypostomus sp. neurocranium (b), both in ventral view. Abbreviations: acm, articular condyle for metapterygoid; af, articular facet for rib on v6; ag, aortic groove; bl, basioccipital lateral process; bo, basioccipital; cc, Weberian complex centrum; ex, exoccipital; exf, exoccipital foramina; fr, frontal; le, lateral ethmoid; ler, lateral ethmoid ridge for metapterygoid; me, mesethmoid; md, mesethmoid disk; os, orbitosphenoid; pr, prootic; ps, parasphenoid; pt, pterotic-supracleithrum; rb, rib; sp, sphenotic?; trl, transcapular ligament; tvp, transverse process of the Weberian compound centrum; v6, sixth vertebrae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5419233" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5419233/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="264">3a</figureCitation>
); parasphenoid wide and flat (
<figureCitation id="137F06C7FFDCAE42FB991EA0C2C5FB33" box="[1148,1221,1180,1203]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[138,177,1901,1924]" captionTargetBox="[151,1445,928,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-404@2.[151,1446,928,1877]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 2. Taubateia paraiba, DGM 17-P, holotype. Shale slab with fossil impression from the Tremembé Formation, Taubaté Basin (a) and the cast in latex (b)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5419231" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5419231/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="264">Figs. 2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="137F06C7FFDCAE42FB2A1EA0C2EAFB33" box="[1231,1258,1180,1203]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[130,169,1778,1801]" captionTargetBox="[165,1431,837,1742]" captionTargetId="figure-433@3.[146,1431,837,1743]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 3. Comparison between an interpretative drawing of Taubateia paraiba (a) and a Hypostomus sp. neurocranium (b), both in ventral view. Abbreviations: acm, articular condyle for metapterygoid; af, articular facet for rib on v6; ag, aortic groove; bl, basioccipital lateral process; bo, basioccipital; cc, Weberian complex centrum; ex, exoccipital; exf, exoccipital foramina; fr, frontal; le, lateral ethmoid; ler, lateral ethmoid ridge for metapterygoid; me, mesethmoid; md, mesethmoid disk; os, orbitosphenoid; pr, prootic; ps, parasphenoid; pt, pterotic-supracleithrum; rb, rib; sp, sphenotic?; trl, transcapular ligament; tvp, transverse process of the Weberian compound centrum; v6, sixth vertebrae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5419233" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5419233/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="264">3a</figureCitation>
); pterotic approximately square and widest at ventral margin(
<figureCitation id="137F06C7FFDCAE42FAEB1E81C358FB54" box="[1294,1368,1213,1236]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[138,177,1901,1924]" captionTargetBox="[151,1445,928,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-404@2.[151,1446,928,1877]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 2. Taubateia paraiba, DGM 17-P, holotype. Shale slab with fossil impression from the Tremembé Formation, Taubaté Basin (a) and the cast in latex (b)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5419231" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5419231/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="264">Figs. 2</figureCitation>
, 
