<subSubSection id="C35E49C9FFDCAE42FCCC1FE3C3A8F9B6" pageId="1" pageNumber="264" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BFB1A42FFDCAE42FCCC1FE3C3A8F9B6" blockId="1.[809,1452,1503,1590]" pageId="1" pageNumber="264">
<emphasis id="B930C650FFDCAE42FCCC1FE3C5A9FA76" bold="true" box="[809,937,1503,1526]" pageId="1" pageNumber="264">Etymology.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C4461C1FFDCAE42FC481FE3C216FA76" authorityName="Malabarba &amp; Lundberg" authorityYear="2007" box="[941,1046,1503,1526]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Taubateia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="264" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B930C650FFDCAE42FC481FE3C216FA76" box="[941,1046,1503,1526]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="264">Taubateia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the name Taubate, in reference to the basin where the fossil comes from, with the suffix “ 
<emphasis id="B930C650FFDCAE42FAB01FC3C369F996" box="[1365,1385,1535,1558]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="264">ia</emphasis>
” from the Latin and Greek, denoting pertaining to; gender feminine.
</paragraph>
